**Visual language**: Follow `010-style-guide.mdc` → Sana Style UI: neutral white/light grey surfaces, sparing blue use, Roboto typography, shared shell components, pill search, ~16-20px card radii. Compare against `design/references/sana/`.

### Critical Setup (ALWAYS verify before implementing)

1. **Canvas Tokens CSS Variables** (REQUIRED in `design/main.tsx`):
   ```tsx
   import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/base/_variables.css';
   import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/system/_variables.css';
   import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/brand/_variables.css';
   ```
   Without these, components appear unstyled.

2. **Canvas Kit Fonts**:
   ```tsx
   import { fonts } from '@workday/canvas-kit-react-fonts';
   <Global styles={css(...fonts, { body: { fontFamily: '"Roboto", sans-serif' } })} />
   ```

### Canvas Kit v14 Components

**Layout**: `Box`, `Flex`, `Card`
**Buttons**: `PrimaryButton`, `SecondaryButton`, `TertiaryButton`, `ToolbarIconButton`
**Inputs**: `TextInput`, `InputGroup`, `FormField`, `Radio`, `Checkbox`
**Display**: `CountBadge`, `Table`, `StatusIndicator`, `Avatar`
**Navigation**: `Tabs`
**Text**: `Heading`, `BodyText`
**Icons**: `SystemIcon`
**Popups**: `Modal`, `Popup`, `Toast`

### Critical v14 APIs

**Tabs**: Use `data-id` (NOT `name`), set `initialTab`:
```tsx
<Tabs initialTab="overview">
  <Tabs.List>
    <Tabs.Item data-id="overview">Overview</Tabs.Item>
  </Tabs.List>
  <Tabs.Panel data-id="overview">Content</Tabs.Panel>
</Tabs>
```

**Table**: Use `.Head`, `.Body`, `.Row`, `.Header`, `.Cell` (NOT HTML elements):
```tsx
<Table>
  <Table.Head>
    <Table.Row>
      <Table.Header>Column</Table.Header>
    </Table.Row>
  </Table.Head>
  <Table.Body>
    <Table.Row>
      <Table.Cell>Data</Table.Cell>
    </Table.Row>
  </Table.Body>
</Table>
```

**FormField**: Composition pattern (`.Label`, `.Input as={...}`):
```tsx
<FormField>
  <FormField.Label htmlFor="id">Label</FormField.Label>
  <FormField.Input as={TextInput} id="id" />
</FormField>
```

**TextInput**: Style props directly on component (NOT via `inputProps`):
```tsx
<TextInput
  value={value}
  onChange={(e) => setValue(e.target.value)}
  style={{ width: '100%' }}
/>
```

### DO/DON'T

**DO**:
- ✅ Verify Canvas Tokens Web CSS variables imported in `design/main.tsx`
- ✅ Use Canvas Kit components exactly as documented in MCP
- ✅ Use `data-id` for Tabs, compound components for Table
- ✅ Call `get-canvas-kit-tokens` for new prototypes
- ✅ Use shared shell components (WorkdayTopNav, WorkdayLeftTabBar, ProfilePageLayout)
- ✅ Use shared form components (FormSelect, FormTextInput, FormDateInput)
- ✅ Reference pattern docs for detailed implementation guidance
